  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best romantic comedy movies?",
  "response": "Romantic comedy movies have been a beloved genre for many years, offering a mix of love, laughter, and often a bit of drama. Here's a list of some of the most popular and critically acclaimed romantic comedies:\n\n1. **\"When Harry Met Sally...\" (1989)** - Directed by Rob Reiner, this film is often considered a classic, exploring the complexities of friendship and romance between two people over many years.\n\n2. **\"Pretty Woman\" (1990)** - Starring Julia Roberts and Richard Gere, this film is a modern Cinderella story with a playful and touching narrative.\n\n3. **\"10 Things I Hate About You\" (1999)** - A modern adaptation of Shakespeare's \"The Taming of the Shrew,\" this teen rom-com features charming performances by Heath Ledger and Julia Stiles.\n\n4. **\"Notting Hill\" (1999)** - Featuring Julia Roberts and Hugh Grant, this movie tells the delightful story of a bookseller who falls in love with a superstar.\n\n5. **\"Bridget Jones's Diary\" (2001)** - Starring Ren\u00e9e Zellweger, Hugh Grant, and Colin Firth, this film follows the humorous life and romantic entanglements of an everyday woman trying to navigate love and career.\n\n6. **\"Love Actually\" (2003)** - A holiday-themed film featuring an ensemble cast, this movie interweaves multiple love stories that explore the intricacies of romance.\n\n7. **\"Crazy, Stupid, Love\" (2011)** - Combining a stellar cast, including Steve Carell, Ryan Gosling, and Emma Stone, this film balances humor with heartfelt moments.\n\n8. **\"The Big Sick\" (2017)** - Based on the real-life romance between writer Emily V. Gordon and comedian Kumail Nanjiani, this film blends cultural themes with a touching love story.\n\n9. **\"To All the Boys I've Loved Before\" (2018)** - A Netflix original that gained immense popularity, it follows the story of a high school girl's secret love letters that are accidentally sent to her crushes.\n\n10. **\"Crazy Rich Asians\" (2018)** - Celebrated for its diverse cast and backdrop against Singapore's opulence, this film gave a fresh perspective on love and family dynamics.\n\nThese films have been widely appreciated for their engaging stories, relatable characters, and the way they capture the ups and downs of love in humorous and heartfelt ways.",
